132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1159
H.P. 764 House of Representatives, March 20, 2025
An Act to Prohibit Businesses from Refusing to Accept Cash for In-
person Payments
Reference to the Committee on Housing and Economic Development suggested and
ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative ROLLINS of Augusta.
Cosponsored by Representatives: BABIN of Fort Fairfield, SINCLAIR of Bath, SUPICA of
Bangor, Senator: DUSON of Cumberland.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 10 MRSA c. 239 is enacted to read:
3 CHAPTER 239
4 PAYMENT BY CASH
5 §1500-Y. Payment by cash
6 A person offering goods or services for sale at retail may not:
7 1. Refuse payment in cash. For sales of less than $2,000, refuse payment in the form
8 of cash for the goods or services;
9 2. Require electronic payment. For sales of less than $2,000, require payment by
10 only an electronic method for the goods or services;
11 3. Sign posting. Post any sign stating that cash payments are not accepted; and
12 4. Higher price. Charge a higher price to customers paying for the goods or services
13 with cash instead of by an electronic method.
14 For purposes of this section, "sale at retail" means any retail transaction conducted in
15 person and does not include a transaction conducted remotely by telephone, mail or the
16 Internet.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This bill requires a person offering goods or services at retail in person to accept cash
1199 for sales of less than $2,000 and prohibits the person from accepting payment by only an
2200 electronic method. These provisions do not apply to transactions conducted remotely by
2211 telephone, mail or the Internet. The bill also prohibits a person offering goods or services
2222 at retail from posting any sign stating that cash payments are not accepted and from
2233 charging a higher price to customers paying with cash instead of by an electronic method.
